deck: Lee Garbett is a British comic book artist. He is the former artist of Fear Itself: the Deep and X-O Manowar. Currently artist on Marvel's Loki: Agent of Asgard.
description:
Lee Garbett is best known for his work on Grant Morrison's Batman: RIP, Last Rites and Return of Bruce Wayne, along with DC's acclaimed re-launch of Batgirl.

Garbett has pencilled some of the biggest characters and titles in the business, including Amazing Spider-Man, Batman & Robin, Justice League Dark, Ghost Rider, Fear Itself, Judge Dredd, Angel and Faith and Ultimate X-Men.

Over the past year Lee has been a regular artist on Valiant's X-O Manowar as well as designing costumes for the forthcoming X-Men Days of Future Past movie. He is currently working with Al Ewing on the All-New Marvel NOW! series Loki: Agent of Asgard.

Links

Lee's blog.

Lee's page on MySpace.
name: Lee Garbett

description:
William Harms is a talented writer with the knack to twist the everyday into a horrific surprise.

He has published works for Marvel Comics, Image Comics, Caliber Press, AiT/PlanetLar, Boneyard Press, and Slave Labor Graphics. His Impaler series was a finalist for the prestigious International Horror Guild award. His latest work is Shotgun Wedding with artist Edward Pun published by Top Cow/Minotaur.

He is currently the lead writer at 2k Games but always finds a way to pen a comic on the side.
name: William Harms
